==English==

===Etymology===
British slang.

===Intransitive Verb===
'''swot'''

# {{UK}}: to study with effort or determination.

===Transitive Verb===
'''swot'''

# {{UK}}: to study something with effort or determination (swot up).

===Noun===
'''swot'''

# {{UK}}: one who swots.
# {{UK}}: [[work]].
# {{UK}}: [[vigorous]] [[study]] at an [[educational institution]].

swot - used in "Perl-XML Frequently Asked Questions" section 2.5 "How to choose a parser module".  Example usage is "You may need to swot up on Perl references (perldoc perlreftut) to take advantage of this module."